Once you have discovered all the IPs (external or internal) you want to scan in depth, different actions can be performed.

Nmap (Network Mapper)

    Basic Ping Scan:

           nmap -sn target.com

SYN Scan:

nmap -sS target.com

Full TCP Scan:

nmap -sT target.com

Service Version Detection:

nmap -sV target.com

Operating System Detection:

nmap -O target.com

Aggressive Scan:

nmap -A target.com

Scan Specific Ports:

nmap -p 22,80,443 target.com

Scan All Ports:

nmap -p- target.com

Script Scanning:

nmap --script vuln target.com


Masscan (Fast Port Scanner)

    Basic Scan:

masscan target.com -p1-65535 --rate=1000


RustScan (Fast Port Scanner)

    Basic Scan:

rustscan -a target.com



Vulnerability Scanning

    Nmap NSE Scripts:
        Heartbleed:

        bash

nmap --script ssl-heartbleed -p 443 target.com

SMB Vulnerabilities:

bash

nmap --script smb-vuln* target.com

HTTP Vulnerabilities:

bash

    nmap --script http-vuln* target.com

OpenVAS:

bash

    openvas-start

        Access via web interface and configure target.
    Nessus:
        Start Nessus service and access via web interface.
        Configure and run a scan on target.com.

Web Application Scanning

    Nikto:

    bash

nikto -h target.com

OWASP ZAP (Zed Attack Proxy):

    Launch OWASP ZAP GUI.
    Configure target and start scan.

Arachni:

bash

    arachni http://target.com --output-only-positives

Specific Protocol Scanning

    FTP:

    bash

nmap -p 21 --script ftp-anon,ftp-bounce,ftp-syst,ftp-vsftpd-backdoor,ftp-proftpd-backdoor target.com

SSH:

bash

nmap -p 22 --script ssh-hostkey,ssh-auth-methods target.com

HTTP:

bash

nmap -p 80,443 --script http-enum,http-title,http-server-header target.com

SMTP:

nmap -p 25 --script smtp-commands,smtp-open-relay,smtp-vuln* target.com

SNMP:

    nmap -sU -p 161 --script snmp-info,snmp-netstat,snmp-processes target.com

Banner Grabbing

    Netcat:

nc -v target.com 80

    Type HEAD / HTTP/1.0 and press Enter twice.

Telnet:

telnet target.com 80

    Type HEAD / HTTP/1.0 and press Enter twice.

Nmap:

nmap -sV --script banner target.com
